objective:
This course will focus on the analysis of big patent data using nature language processing. Material covered will integrate the five key facets of an investigation using open Patent data:
(1) Patent Data collection - data wrangling, cleaning, and sampling to get a suitable data set; 
(2) Patent Data processing and visualization –practicing data transformation based on linear algebra; 
(3) Exploratory Patent data analysis – generating hypotheses and building intuition; 
(4) Mathematical NLP Models - statistical learning and classification; 
(5) Prediction - decision trees and linear regression. The curriculum for this course builds for the advanced machine learning courses. Students are strongly encouraged to utilize Python to enhance their programming capability.
